#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid ""
"A standard education entry includes four elements: the degree name, the institution name, the location, and the graduation date (or expected graduation date). For example: \"Bachelor of Science in Computer Science, Mohammed V University, Rabat, Morocco, June 2024.\"\n"
"\n"
"The degree name should be written out formally. Use \"Bachelor of Science\" rather than \"BS\" or \"B.Sc.\" for clarity, though abbreviations are acceptable if space is tight. Include your major and minor if the minor is relevant to the position. Double majors should both be listed.\n"
"\n"
"For the graduation date, recent graduates should include the month and year. Experienced professionals can list just the year, and those who graduated more than 15 years ago may choose to omit the date entirely to avoid age-related bias. If you are still in school, write \"Expected June 2027\" or \"In Progress\" with the anticipated completion date.\n"
"\n"
"Beyond these basics, you may add relevant coursework, academic honors (Dean's List, cum laude), thesis or capstone project titles, study abroad experiences, or extracurricular leadership roles. These additions are most valuable for students and recent graduates. As your career progresses, trim these details to keep the section concise and focused on the degree itself.\n"
"\n"
"If you attended a university but did not complete the degree, you can still list it. Write the institution name, the area of study, and the dates attended, followed by a note such as \"Coursework completed toward a Bachelor of Arts in Economics, 2019-2021.\" This is honest and still shows relevant academic exposure."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/networking-linkedin.ts
msgid "A strong LinkedIn profile photo is a high-resolution headshot with good lighting, a clean background, and professional attire appropriate to your industry. Your face should fill about 60 percent of the frame, and your expression should be approachable yet confident. Avoid group photos, casual selfies, or heavily filtered images. Consider having a professional headshot taken, as this small investment yields significant returns in profile engagement."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid ""
"A surprising number of cover letters read like a wish list of what the candidate wants from the job rather than a proposal of what the candidate can offer the employer. Phrases like \"I am looking for an opportunity to develop my skills in data science\" or \"This role would help me transition into the management track I have always wanted\" center the narrative on your needs, not the employer's.\n"
"\n"
"Hiring managers are not evaluating candidates based on who needs the job the most -- they are looking for the person who will deliver the most value to their organization. Every claim in your cover letter should be framed in terms of the benefit to the employer. Instead of \"I want to learn about machine learning,\" write \"My strong foundation in statistical analysis and my self-directed study of machine learning algorithms position me to contribute to your team's predictive modeling initiatives from day one.\"\n"
"\n"
"This does not mean you cannot express enthusiasm or career aspirations. It means framing those aspirations in a way that aligns with the employer's interests. \"I am particularly drawn to this role because your company's focus on accessibility in healthcare technology aligns with my lifelong commitment to equitable access\" shows personal motivation while simultaneously demonstrating cultural fit.\n"
"\n"
"To check whether your letter is properly employer-focused, count the ratio of \"I\" statements to \"you/your\" statements. If the letter is overwhelmingly about you, revise to incorporate more references to the company, the team, and the specific challenges or opportunities of the role. The best cover letters create a bridge between your capabilities and the employer's needs."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/dashboard/networking/-components/message-templates-config.ts
msgid "A thank you message should be sent promptly after the interview or meeting to remain memorable."
msgstr "Un message de remerciement doit être envoyé rapidement après l'entretien ou la réunion pour rester mémorable."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "A thorough guide to building resumes for finance, accounting, banking, and financial analysis roles. Covers certifications, quantitative achievements, regulatory knowledge, and industry-specific formatting."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid ""
"A tools and equipment section is essential for skilled trades resumes and has no true equivalent in most other industries. This section serves as a quick reference that allows employers to verify you have hands-on experience with the specific tools and systems they use in their operations. It also helps with keyword matching in applicant tracking systems, which are increasingly used even in blue-collar hiring.\n"
"\n"
"Organize your tools list by category for easy scanning. An electrician might group tools into categories such as hand tools, power tools, testing and diagnostic equipment, and specialized equipment. A plumber might separate hand tools, power equipment, testing devices, and heavy equipment. Within each category, list specific items rather than generic categories. Write Fluke 87V multimeter rather than just multimeter, or Hilti TE 60 rotary hammer rather than just hammer drill, as brand-specific knowledge signals professional-level experience.\n"
"\n"
"Beyond hand and power tools, include any specialized equipment, vehicles, or technology platforms you are qualified to operate. This might include forklifts, boom lifts, excavators, welding machines of specific types (MIG, TIG, stick, flux-core), CNC machines, PLC programming interfaces, building automation systems, or computerized maintenance management systems (CMMS). If you hold specific equipment certifications or operator licenses, cross-reference these with your certifications section.\n"
"\n"
"For maintenance and facilities technicians, include the building systems and equipment types you have experience maintaining. This might encompass boiler systems, chillers, cooling towers, fire alarm and suppression systems, emergency generators, electrical distribution panels, plumbing systems, and building envelope components. The breadth of systems experience is particularly important for facilities maintenance roles, where employers need technicians who can troubleshoot across multiple trades rather than specialists in a single discipline."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid ""
"A two-page resume is appropriate and often expected for experienced professionals whose careers have accumulated enough relevant achievements, skills, and credentials to warrant the additional space. If you find yourself cutting important, relevant content simply to squeeze onto one page, that is a strong signal that a two-page resume is the right choice.\n"
"\n"
"Senior professionals with 10 or more years of experience often have multiple significant roles, each with accomplishments worth highlighting. Forcing this depth of experience into one page means either cutting impressive achievements or shrinking the font to an unreadable size. Neither option serves you well. Two pages give you the space to provide appropriate detail for your most recent roles while still listing earlier positions.\n"
"\n"
"Managers and executives who oversee large teams, manage substantial budgets, or lead complex initiatives need space to convey the scope and impact of their work. A VP of Engineering who has led teams of 200 engineers, managed a $50 million budget, and delivered three major product launches cannot adequately describe this experience in three bullet points. Two pages allow the depth of description these positions require.\n"
"\n"
"Professionals in technical fields such as engineering, IT, data science, or healthcare often need a second page to list technical skills, certifications, tools, and methodologies alongside their work experience. A software architect who is proficient in 15 programming languages and frameworks, holds three cloud certifications, and has contributed to major open-source projects needs the space to present these qualifications comprehensively.\n"
"\n"
"Candidates applying for federal government positions in the United States are expected to submit detailed resumes that often extend to three or more pages. Government resumes follow specific formatting guidelines that require comprehensive descriptions of duties, accomplishments, and hours worked per week. If you are applying for a government position, research the specific requirements of the agency and follow them precisely."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "A typical counter-offer is 10 to 20 percent above the initial offer, depending on how far below market rate the offer is. Your counter should be grounded in research data, not an arbitrary percentage. If the offer is already near the top of the market range, a modest counter of 5 to 10 percent is more appropriate. The key is that your number should be justifiable with data."
msgstr ""

