#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Aim for 8 to 15 skills, focusing on those most relevant to the target position. For technical roles, you may include more if they are well-organized into categories. The goal is to present a focused, credible list rather than an exhaustive inventory. Every skill listed should be one you can confidently discuss in an interview."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Aim for at least three to five independent sources to build a reliable salary range. Using multiple sources helps you identify the true market range by finding where the data overlaps, and it gives you more credibility during the negotiation when you can reference several data points rather than a single source."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Aim for data that is no more than 12 months old, and ideally within the last 6 months. Compensation markets can shift rapidly due to economic conditions, industry growth, and talent supply changes. Government data like BLS statistics may lag by 12 to 18 months, so use it as a baseline but supplement with more current sources like Glassdoor and LinkedIn."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid "Aim for two to four informational interviews per week during an active search. This volume builds momentum, expands your network rapidly, and increases the probability of discovering hidden opportunities. Each conversation typically leads to one to two additional referrals, creating a compounding effect that accelerates your access to the hidden job market over time."
msgstr ""

