#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid ""
"Creating an effective combination resume requires strategic thinking and meticulous execution. Begin by researching your target roles thoroughly. Read multiple job postings for similar positions and identify the recurring themes, skills, and qualifications that appear across them. These recurring elements should form the foundation of your skills categories. Aligning your resume with what employers are consistently asking for dramatically increases your chances of passing both ATS screening and human review.\n"
"\n"
"When building your skills categories, choose names that are specific enough to be meaningful but broad enough to encompass multiple achievements. \"Project Management\" is a good category name because it clearly communicates a domain of expertise while allowing you to include examples from different contexts. \"Miscellaneous Skills\" is too vague, while \"SAP ERP Implementation Project Management\" is so specific that it limits what you can include underneath.\n"
"\n"
"Avoid duplicating content between your skills section and your work experience section. Each section should complement the other rather than repeat the same information. Use your skills section for your most impactful, cross-cutting achievements, and use your work experience section for role-specific accomplishments that provide additional context. Think of the skills section as your highlight reel and the work experience section as the supporting documentation.\n"
"\n"
"Pay careful attention to keywords throughout your combination resume. ATS software scans for specific terms from the job description, so incorporating relevant keywords naturally into both your skills section and your work experience section is essential. However, do not sacrifice readability for keyword density. Keyword stuffing is detectable by both sophisticated ATS systems and human readers, and it will undermine your credibility.\n"
"\n"
"Format your combination resume for easy scanning. Use consistent headings, clear section dividers, and adequate white space. Recruiters typically spend six to seven seconds on an initial resume scan, so your most important qualifications need to be visible immediately. Bold your skill category headings, use bullet points rather than paragraphs for individual achievements, and ensure that your font size and spacing make the document comfortable to read.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, have your combination resume reviewed by someone who works in your target industry or a professional resume writer. Because the combination format is more complex than a straightforward chronological resume, it benefits from a second pair of eyes to ensure the structure is logical, the content is compelling, and the overall presentation is polished. A well-executed combination resume is one of the most powerful tools in a job seeker's arsenal."
msgstr ""

