msgid "Entry-Level Resume: How to Stand Out With No Experience"
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid ""
"Entry-level salary research requires some different approaches compared to mid-career research. General salary databases like Glassdoor and LinkedIn are helpful starting points, but they often have limited data for entry-level positions because fewer employees at that level contribute salary information. Supplement these sources with resources specifically designed for new graduates.\n"
"\n"
"University career centers are among the most underutilized salary research resources available to new graduates. Most career centers conduct annual surveys of graduating students and publish reports on starting salaries by major, degree level, and industry. These reports provide highly relevant benchmarks because they reflect the actual offers received by your peers in your specific program and geographic market.\n"
"\n"
"The National Association of Colleges and Employers (NACE) publishes comprehensive salary survey data for entry-level positions broken down by degree, major, industry, and region. Many professional associations also publish entry-level salary guides specific to their field. These targeted resources provide much more relevant data than general salary databases for someone just starting their career.\n"
"\n"
"Talk to recent alumni from your program who graduated one to three years before you. They can share not only what they were offered but also what they negotiated, what they wish they had known, and how their compensation has progressed since starting. This qualitative intelligence is invaluable and often more actionable than database statistics.\n"
"\n"
"When researching, pay attention to total compensation, not just base salary. Many entry-level positions in technology, consulting, and finance include significant signing bonuses, relocation packages, and equity that substantially increase total first-year earnings. An offer with a slightly lower base salary but a generous signing bonus and equity grant may be worth considerably more in total."
msgstr ""

