#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Generally no, once you have a college degree. The exception is if a high school achievement is extraordinarily notable, such as a national competition win, a patent, or a published work that remains relevant to your career direction. Otherwise, your college education and experiences should fully replace high school content."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid "Generally, no. Apply through the company's direct career page when possible, as this is usually the preferred channel. If you find a position on multiple boards, choose the one most likely to route directly to the hiring team. Duplicate applications from different platforms can create confusion in the employer's tracking system and may reflect poorly on your attention to detail."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Generally, no. Once you have completed any form of higher education (university, community college, trade school, or professional certification), high school should be removed from your resume. The only exception is if you are a current high school student or recent graduate who has not yet started any post-secondary education."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Generally, your chronological resume should cover the last 10 to 15 years of relevant work experience. For most professionals, this translates to three to five positions. Including roles from more than 15 years ago can make your resume feel dated and risks age discrimination. However, if an earlier role is highly relevant to the position you are applying for, you can include it in a brief \"Earlier Experience\" section without detailed bullet points."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid "Generally, your resume should cover the last 10 to 15 years of relevant work experience. For most hiring managers, anything older than that is less relevant to your current capabilities. If you have earlier experience that is particularly impressive or directly relevant to the role, you can include a brief \"Earlier Career\" section with condensed entries. Recent graduates should include all relevant experience, including internships, part-time work, and significant academic projects."
msgstr ""

