#: src/data/wiki/categories/remote-work.ts
msgid ""
"If you have previous remote work experience, feature it prominently. Specify that previous roles were remote by including \"Remote\" as the location or adding a note like \"Fully remote role serving a distributed team across 12 time zones.\" This immediately signals to the hiring manager that you have navigated the unique challenges of remote work and do not require a transition period.\n"
"\n"
"For each remote role, emphasize accomplishments that demonstrate remote-specific competencies. Instead of simply listing responsibilities, highlight outcomes that required self-management, asynchronous communication, or cross-timezone collaboration. For example, \"Led a distributed team of 8 engineers across 4 time zones to deliver a platform migration on schedule and under budget\" tells a more compelling remote story than \"Managed engineering team for platform migration.\"\n"
"\n"
"Digital tool proficiency is table stakes for remote roles. Create a dedicated skills section or integrate tool expertise throughout your experience descriptions. Key tools to highlight include project management platforms like Asana, Jira, Monday.com, and Trello; communication tools like Slack, Microsoft Teams, and Zoom; collaboration tools like Notion, Confluence, Miro, and Figma; and version control or documentation systems relevant to your field. Do not simply list tools; show how you used them to achieve results.\n"
"\n"
"If you lack formal remote work experience, identify aspects of your in-office roles that involved remote-adjacent skills. Managing vendors in different locations, collaborating with offshore teams, leading virtual meetings, working with distributed clients, or contributing to projects during work-from-home periods all count as relevant remote experience. Reframe these experiences to highlight the remote competencies they required.\n"
"\n"
"Document any remote-specific training, certifications, or courses you have completed. Certifications in remote project management, virtual team leadership, or digital collaboration demonstrate proactive investment in remote work skills. Even completing courses on platforms like Coursera, LinkedIn Learning, or Udemy shows initiative and self-directed learning, which are core remote work values."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/dashboard/networking/-components/recommendation-request-config.ts
msgid "If you haven't heard back a week before the deadline, send a courteous reminder."
msgstr "Si vous n'avez pas eu de retour une semaine avant l'échéance, envoyez un rappel courtois."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid "If you hold an active security clearance, list it prominently on your resume, as it is a significant asset for many employers, particularly in defense, government contracting, and technology sectors. Simply state the clearance level and whether it is current. Do not include any classified details about your work. An active clearance saves employers significant time and money on the vetting process."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid ""
"If you hold multiple degrees, list them in reverse chronological order, with the highest or most recent degree first. A Master's degree should appear above a Bachelor's degree. If both degrees are from the same institution, you can group them under a single institution header with separate entries for each degree.\n"
"\n"
"Professional certifications can be listed in the education section or in a separate certifications section, depending on their importance and quantity. If you have one or two certifications that are closely tied to your formal education, grouping them with education makes sense. If you have several professional certifications, a dedicated section keeps the resume organized.\n"
"\n"
"Ongoing education shows commitment to growth. If you are currently enrolled in a degree program, certification course, or professional development program, include it with an expected completion date. Online courses from platforms like Coursera, edX, or professional training providers can be included if they are relevant and from reputable institutions.\n"
"\n"
"Boot camps and intensive training programs are increasingly respected by employers, especially in technology. List them as you would any educational program: program name, institution, and completion date. Including a capstone project or portfolio piece from the program adds credibility.\n"
"\n"
"For candidates with education from multiple countries, be consistent in how you present degrees and institutions. If your degree title might be unfamiliar to the target audience, include a brief parenthetical explanation: \"Licence Fondamentale (equivalent to Bachelor's degree) in Business Administration.\""
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/interview-preparation.ts
msgid ""
"If you receive a rejection after the interview, respond with grace and professionalism. Thank the interviewer for the opportunity, express your disappointment, and ask if they would be willing to provide feedback on your interview performance. Many hiring managers appreciate this approach and will share constructive insights that help you improve. Additionally, maintaining a positive relationship keeps the door open for future opportunities with the organization.\n"
"\n"
"When you receive a job offer, respond within the timeframe the employer specifies, typically twenty-four to seventy-two hours. Even if you are thrilled about the offer, take time to review the complete compensation package before accepting. Express your gratitude and enthusiasm while asking for the offer in writing if it was communicated verbally. If you need to negotiate salary or benefits, do so respectfully and with supporting market data.\n"
"\n"
"If you are waiting on multiple opportunities simultaneously, keep each employer informed as necessary without revealing details about the other companies. You might say \"I want to be transparent that I am in the final stages with another opportunity, and I am very interested in your role. Could you let me know your timeline for a decision?\" This creates urgency without seeming manipulative and gives the employer the chance to accelerate their process.\n"
"\n"
"For follow-ups after a second or third round interview, the same principles apply but with increased urgency and specificity. By this stage, you have invested significant time in the process and have a deeper understanding of the role. Your follow-up communications should reflect this depth by referencing specific conversations, addressing any remaining questions the hiring team may have, and painting a clear picture of the value you would bring to the organization."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/_home/help.tsx
#~ msgid "If you're a recent graduate or student, yes, include your baccalaureat with the type (science, technique, etc.) and year. Once you have more professional experience, you can remove it to save space."
#~ msgstr "Si vous êtes un jeune diplômé ou étudiant, oui, incluez votre baccalauréat avec le type (science, technique, etc.) et l'année. Une fois que vous avez plus d'expérience professionnelle, vous pouvez le retirer pour gagner de la place."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid ""
"If your resume has grown beyond your target length, strategic editing can help you trim it without sacrificing impact. The goal is to remove the least relevant content while preserving the achievements and qualifications that make the strongest case for your candidacy.\n"
"\n"
"Start by eliminating any content that does not directly support your application for the target role. If a bullet point describes a responsibility that is not relevant to the position you are seeking, remove it regardless of how proud you are of that accomplishment. Every line on your resume must earn its place by answering the question, \"Does this make me a more compelling candidate for this specific job?\"\n"
"\n"
"Consolidate similar bullet points that describe related accomplishments. If you have three bullet points about different aspects of the same project, consider combining them into one comprehensive point. \"Led the CRM migration project, transitioning 50,000 customer records, training 120 end users, and achieving zero data loss during the cutover weekend\" is more powerful than three separate bullets describing each aspect.\n"
"\n"
"Reduce or eliminate older positions that no longer define your professional identity. If your most recent three roles are in product management, you do not need detailed bullet points for the customer service job you held 15 years ago. List earlier positions with just the title, company, and dates, or group them under a \"Previous Experience\" heading with a single line each.\n"
"\n"
"Tighten your language by removing filler words and redundant phrases. \"Successfully managed\" can become \"Managed.\" \"Was responsible for the development and implementation of\" can become \"Developed and implemented.\" \"Utilized various tools and technologies to\" can become the specific tools and technologies you used. These small edits add up quickly and can free significant space across your resume.\n"
"\n"
"Adjust formatting strategically. Reducing margins slightly (to 0.5 inches), using a slightly smaller but still readable font size (10 or 10.5 point), or reducing the space between sections can reclaim space without sacrificing readability. However, never push formatting adjustments to the point where the document looks cramped. Readability always takes priority over length."
msgstr ""

