#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid "Include the last 10 to 15 years of experience, but focus your detailed descriptions on roles and achievements that are most relevant to your target career. Older or less relevant positions can be listed briefly with just the job title, company, and dates. The goal is to show a coherent narrative that leads naturally to your new career direction."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Include them if they demonstrate transferable skills, fill an employment gap, or show career progression. If a past role is completely unrelated and you have enough relevant experience, you can omit it or condense it to a single line with just the title, company, and dates. Never leave unexplained gaps if the omission creates one."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Include them in the context of specific project descriptions rather than in your standalone skills section. For example, you might write that you integrated a Redis caching layer to reduce API response times, which communicates your exposure to Redis without claiming deep expertise. Reserve your skills section for technologies you could discuss confidently in a technical interview."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/remote-work.ts
msgid "Include your city and state or country, but a full street address is unnecessary for remote positions. Your location matters because many remote roles have geographic restrictions related to taxes, labor laws, or time zone requirements. If you are open to relocating or working in any time zone, mention that flexibility explicitly to broaden your opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/dashboard/tools/-components/linkedin-components.tsx
msgid "Include your current role + specialty + added value"
msgstr "Incluez votre poste actuel + spécialité + valeur ajoutée"

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Include your GPA if it is 3.0 or higher on a 4.0 scale, or the equivalent in your grading system. If your major GPA is significantly higher than your cumulative GPA, you may list your major GPA instead. After two to three years of professional experience, GPA becomes less relevant and can be removed."
