#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Proficiency levels can be useful for language skills and certain technical competencies where the distinction between beginner and expert matters. However, avoid subjective rating systems like progress bars, which have no universal standard and cannot be parsed by ATS systems. If you use proficiency labels, stick to widely understood terms like \"native,\" \"fluent,\" \"proficient,\" or \"familiar.\""
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid ""
"Proficiency with electronic health record systems and healthcare technology has become a baseline requirement for nearly every clinical role. Hospitals and health systems have invested billions in EHR platforms, and they need staff who can navigate these systems efficiently without extensive retraining. Including specific EHR and technology skills on your resume is no longer optional; it is expected.\n"
"\n"
"Name the specific EHR platforms you have used, such as Epic, Cerner, Meditech, Allscripts, or athenahealth. If you have experience with multiple platforms, list all of them, as this versatility is highly valued by organizations that have recently undergone system transitions or acquisitions. Beyond the core EHR, mention any specialized modules or functionalities you have worked with, such as computerized provider order entry, clinical decision support tools, barcode medication administration, telehealth platforms, or patient portal management.\n"
"\n"
"For clinical roles that involve medical devices or specialized technology, create a separate skills subsection that lists the equipment and systems you are competent with. This might include ventilators, infusion pumps, cardiac monitors, imaging equipment, surgical navigation systems, or point-of-care testing devices. Biomedical engineers and health IT professionals should list the systems they have configured, maintained, or implemented, along with any relevant vendor certifications.\n"
"\n"
"If you have participated in EHR implementation projects, system upgrades, or workflow optimization initiatives, describe your role and the outcomes achieved. Healthcare organizations frequently struggle with technology adoption, and candidates who have experience as super users, trainers, or implementation team members bring significant value beyond their clinical skills. Quantify your impact where possible, such as noting that you trained forty-five staff members on a new charting module and achieved a ninety-two percent adoption rate within the first month of go-live."
msgstr ""

