#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid ""
"Structuring a chronological resume requires careful attention to hierarchy and detail. The goal is to present your information in a clean, scannable format that guides the reader from your most impressive qualifications down to supporting details. Start with a strong header that includes your full name, professional email address, phone number, LinkedIn profile URL, and optionally your city and state or region.\n"
"\n"
"Immediately following your header, include a professional summary or career objective. A professional summary is a brief paragraph of three to five sentences that highlights your most relevant skills, years of experience, and key accomplishments. This section acts as your elevator pitch and should be tailored to the specific job you are applying for. For experienced professionals, a summary is more appropriate; for entry-level candidates, a career objective that states your goals and enthusiasm can be effective.\n"
"\n"
"The work experience section is the heart of your chronological resume. List each position starting with your most recent role. For each entry, include your job title, the name of the company, the location of the company, and your dates of employment. Below these details, include four to six bullet points describing your responsibilities and achievements. Use strong action verbs to begin each bullet point, and quantify your accomplishments wherever possible. Instead of writing \"responsible for managing a team,\" write \"led a team of 12 engineers, delivering three major product releases on schedule and under budget.\"\n"
"\n"
"After your work experience, include your education section. List your degrees in reverse chronological order, including the institution name, degree type, field of study, and graduation date. If you graduated with honors or achieved a notable GPA, include that information. For professionals with more than five years of experience, the education section typically receives less emphasis than work experience.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, add optional sections that strengthen your candidacy. These might include technical skills, certifications, professional affiliations, languages spoken, volunteer experience, or publications. Keep these sections concise and relevant to the position you are targeting. Every element on your chronological resume should serve the purpose of demonstrating your fit for the role."
msgstr ""

