#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid ""
"The ATS market includes dozens of platforms, each with different parsing capabilities, scoring algorithms, and user interfaces. Knowing which systems are most prevalent can help you understand what your resume is up against. The most widely used ATS platforms include Workday, Taleo (now part of Oracle), Greenhouse, Lever, iCIMS, BambooHR, JazzHR, and SAP SuccessFactors.\n"
"\n"
"Workday is especially common among large enterprises and Fortune 500 companies. Its recruiting module is tightly integrated with human capital management features, making it a popular choice for organizations that want an all-in-one HR platform. Taleo, one of the oldest ATS solutions, remains widely used despite its reputation for a clunky candidate experience. Greenhouse and Lever are favorites among technology companies and startups, known for their modern interfaces and structured hiring workflows.\n"
"\n"
"iCIMS serves a broad market from mid-size companies to large enterprises and is particularly strong in healthcare, education, and government sectors. BambooHR and JazzHR cater to smaller businesses that need affordable yet functional applicant tracking. SAP SuccessFactors is prevalent in global corporations that already use SAP for enterprise resource planning.\n"
"\n"
"Each of these platforms has slightly different parsing engines and scoring methodologies. However, the fundamental principles of ATS optimization remain consistent across all of them: use standard formatting, include relevant keywords, choose compatible file types, and organize your content with clear section headings. A resume that is optimized for one major ATS will generally perform well across all of them because the underlying parsing technologies share common approaches to document analysis."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/job-search-strategies.ts
msgid ""
"The average active job seeker applies to 50 to 100 positions during their search, and without a tracking system, it is impossible to manage the details, deadlines, and follow-ups for that volume of applications. Tracking transforms your search from a chaotic collection of browser tabs and email threads into an organized project with clear status updates and actionable next steps.\n"
"\n"
"Application tracking provides the data you need to make strategic decisions about your search. Without tracking, you cannot calculate your conversion rates, identify which channels produce the most interviews, or determine which types of roles respond most positively to your applications. This data is essential for course-correcting a search that is not producing results.\n"
"\n"
"Timely follow-up is one of the most impactful and most frequently missed activities in a job search. Studies show that a single well-timed follow-up can increase your response rate by 30 to 50 percent, but without a tracking system, follow-up dates slip past and opportunities are lost. A good tracking system automatically surfaces follow-up reminders so you never miss a critical window.\n"
"\n"
"Professional organization also shows in your interactions with employers. When a recruiter calls unexpectedly about a position you applied to three weeks ago, being able to immediately reference the role, the job description details, and any prior communication demonstrates professionalism and genuine interest. Fumbling to remember which position they are calling about makes a poor impression."
msgstr ""

