#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid ""
"The structure of a healthcare resume should prioritize clinical qualifications and direct patient care experience above all else. Start with a professional summary that immediately identifies your role, specialty area, years of experience, and one or two headline accomplishments. For example, a registered nurse might open with a summary stating their specialty in critical care, their years of ICU experience, and a notable achievement such as reducing catheter-associated infection rates by a measurable percentage.\n"
"\n"
"Immediately following the summary, include a dedicated section for licenses and certifications. This is non-negotiable in healthcare. List your primary license first, including the state of issuance and expiration date, followed by certifications in order of relevance to the target position. Common certifications that recruiters search for include BLS, ACLS, PALS, TNCC, and specialty certifications from bodies such as the ANCC or AACN. Including expiration dates demonstrates that you actively maintain your credentials and stay current with continuing education requirements.\n"
"\n"
"Your clinical experience section should be formatted to highlight the facility type, unit or department, patient population, and bed count where applicable. Each role entry should include three to six bullet points that combine action verbs with quantifiable outcomes. Instead of writing that you provided patient care, specify that you managed a caseload of twelve to fifteen patients per shift in a Level I trauma center and achieved a patient satisfaction score in the ninetieth percentile. This level of specificity reassures hiring managers that you can perform at the level their facility demands.\n"
"\n"
"Education should follow clinical experience for experienced professionals, but new graduates may place education higher since clinical rotations and capstone projects are their primary proof of competency. Include the name of your nursing or medical program, the degree earned, graduation date, and any academic honors. If you completed clinical rotations at prestigious institutions or specialized units, list those rotations with the hours completed and the skills developed during each placement."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/career-transitions.ts
msgid ""
"The structure of your resume should be designed to lead with your most marketable qualities while providing clear context for your military background.\n"
"\n"
"Open with a strong professional summary that positions you as a civilian professional. State your years of experience, your key competencies in civilian terms, and your target role or industry. For example: \"Operations and logistics leader with 10 years of experience managing teams of up to 50 personnel, overseeing multimillion-dollar equipment inventories, and executing complex projects in high-pressure environments. Seeking a supply chain management role in the manufacturing sector.\"\n"
"\n"
"Create a skills section that highlights your most transferable competencies. Common military-to-civilian transferable skills include leadership and team management, strategic planning and execution, risk assessment and mitigation, logistics and supply chain management, training and personnel development, budget management, communication and briefing, crisis management, and technology proficiency.\n"
"\n"
"In your experience section, list each military position with a translated job title followed by your actual rank and unit in parentheses if you choose. This approach gives civilian readers an immediate understanding of your role while preserving the specifics of your service for those who understand military structure.\n"
"\n"
"Quantify everything you can. Military experience often involves impressive numbers: personnel managed, budgets controlled, equipment valued, operations conducted, and improvements achieved. These metrics speak a universal language. \"Managed logistics operations for a $12 million equipment inventory\" is meaningful to any hiring manager, regardless of whether they understand the military context."
msgstr ""

