#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, absolutely. Many professional resume designers prioritize visual impact over ATS compatibility. Beautifully designed resumes with custom layouts, graphics, tables, and creative formatting often perform poorly in ATS systems. If your professionally designed resume uses multi-column layouts, text boxes, images, or non-standard section headings, it may fail to parse correctly. Ask your designer specifically about ATS compatibility, or maintain a separate ATS-optimized version of your resume for online applications. Use creative designs only for networking and in-person opportunities."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, and this approach is called a combination or hybrid resume. It is increasingly popular because it allows you to lead with a skills section that highlights your most relevant competencies while still including a chronological work history section that provides context and credibility. The combination format addresses the main weakness of the functional resume, which is the lack of context for your accomplishments, while still giving you the flexibility to emphasize your skills."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, combination resumes are generally ATS-compatible because they include the standard chronological work history section that ATS systems are designed to parse. The addition of a skills section at the top does not confuse most modern ATS software. To maximize compatibility, use standard section headings, avoid tables or complex formatting, and include relevant keywords from the job description throughout both the skills and experience sections."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, cover letters remain expected for most finance positions, particularly at banks, accounting firms, and corporate finance departments. A strong cover letter allows you to explain your specific interest in the firm and role, contextualize career transitions, and demonstrate written communication skills. Keep it concise, ideally three to four paragraphs, and tailor it to each application rather than using a generic template."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, depending on how the employer has configured the system. Some ATS platforms allow employers to set minimum score thresholds or knockout questions that automatically disqualify candidates who do not meet basic requirements. However, many companies configure their ATS to rank rather than reject, meaning a recruiter can still access lower-scoring resumes if they choose to. The safest approach is to optimize your resume so it scores well regardless of the system's configuration."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, especially if you are a new graduate or have fewer than two years of post-licensure experience. List each rotation with the facility name, unit type, hours completed, and key skills developed. As you gain more professional experience, clinical rotations can be condensed or moved to an education subsection."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, especially if you are a recent graduate or early in your career. Professors who supervised your research, capstone projects, or internships can provide credible references about your work ethic, analytical skills, and potential. As your career progresses, aim to replace academic references with professional ones from supervisors and colleagues."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Yes, even companies with standardized benefits often have flexibility, especially for senior hires. While health insurance plans and retirement matching may be truly fixed, signing bonuses, equity grants, PTO above the standard allotment, and professional development budgets are frequently negotiable. The key is asking, because many candidates assume everything is fixed when it is not."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, for maximum ATS compatibility, use the exact terminology from the job description wherever possible. If the posting says \"project management,\" use \"project management\" rather than \"managing projects.\" If it mentions a specific tool like \"Salesforce CRM,\" use that exact phrase. However, also include common variations and abbreviations, such as writing out \"Search Engine Optimization (SEO)\" on first use. This covers both exact-match and semantic-match algorithms. Always ensure that any keyword you include truthfully represents your skills and experience."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/remote-work.ts
msgid "Yes, having notes nearby is one advantage of virtual interviews. Place key talking points, company research, and questions on a small note next to your camera so you can reference them without obviously looking away. Avoid reading directly from notes, as this is noticeable on camera. Use them as memory prompts for prepared stories and data points, not as a script to read verbatim."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, if the certification is relevant to the target role and you are actively working toward it. List it with \"In Progress\" or \"Expected [Month Year]\" to set clear expectations. This shows initiative and signals that you will soon hold the credential. However, do not list certifications you have only vaguely planned to pursue someday."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/networking-linkedin.ts
msgid "Yes, if you meet approximately 60 to 70 percent of the listed requirements. Job descriptions often represent an ideal candidate rather than a minimum requirement. Skills can be learned, and transferable experience from different industries or roles can be equally valuable. Focus your application on the requirements you do meet, explain how your transferable skills compensate for any gaps, and express enthusiasm for growing in the areas where you have less experience."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, if your GitHub profile contains relevant, well-maintained repositories that demonstrate your coding ability. Ensure your pinned repositories are current, well-documented, and representative of the work you want to be known for. If your GitHub is sparse or contains only forked repositories with no contributions, it may be better to omit it or create a few meaningful projects before including it."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/salary-negotiation.ts
msgid "Yes, in most cases. Even a fair offer typically has some negotiation room built in, and a polite, well-researched counter demonstrates professionalism. You can acknowledge the offer is competitive while asking if there is flexibility on specific components. Even small gains in base salary compound significantly over your career."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/industry-guides.ts
msgid "Yes, include your union affiliation, local number, and membership status, especially when applying to union shops or projects with prevailing wage requirements. Union membership signals formal training, adherence to industry standards, and access to a verified dispatch system. For non-union applications, you may still include it as it demonstrates professional commitment, though it is not required."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-sections.ts
msgid "Yes, particularly if the courses are from recognized institutions or platforms and are directly relevant to the position. For one or two courses, the education section works fine. If you have many, consider a separate \"Professional Development\" or \"Certifications\" section to keep the education section focused on formal degrees."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/_home/-sections/faq.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes, IMTA Resume is available in multiple languages. You can choose your preferred language in the settings page, or using the language switcher in the top right corner. If you don't see your language, or you would like to improve the existing translations, you can <0>contribute to the translations on Crowdin<1> (opens in new tab)</1></0>."
#~ msgstr "Oui, IMTA Resume est disponible en plusieurs langues. Vous pouvez choisir votre langue préférée dans la page des paramètres, ou en utilisant le sélecteur de langue dans le coin supérieur droit. Si vous ne voyez pas votre langue, ou si vous souhaitez améliorer les traductions existantes, vous pouvez <0>contribuer aux traductions sur Crowdin<1> (s'ouvre dans un nouvel onglet)</1></0>."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid "Yes, stating that you will follow up is generally appropriate and demonstrates initiative. A line such as \"I will follow up next week to confirm you received my application\" shows proactive interest without being aggressive. However, if the job posting explicitly states \"no phone calls\" or \"we will contact qualified candidates,\" respect those boundaries and instead express your availability without committing to a specific follow-up action."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, the resume format matters because it determines how effectively your qualifications are communicated to the reader. The right format highlights your strengths and minimizes weaknesses, while the wrong format can obscure your best qualifications or draw attention to areas of concern. However, format alone does not determine success. Strong, specific, and quantified content is the most important factor. Think of the format as the packaging: it should make the content easy to access and understand, but it is the content that ultimately wins the job."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/_home/help.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes, the resume will automatically flow to additional pages if needed. However, for entry-level positions, keeping it to one page is recommended. Experienced professionals can use two pages."
#~ msgstr "Oui, le CV s'étendra automatiquement sur des pages supplémentaires si nécessaire. Cependant, pour les postes de débutant, il est recommandé de s'en tenir à une page. Les professionnels expérimentés peuvent utiliser deux pages."

#: src/data/wiki/categories/interview-preparation.ts
msgid "Yes, the STAR framework can be adapted for many types of interview questions. Even when asked about your strengths or why you want the role, incorporating a brief STAR example makes your answer more concrete and credible. For hypothetical or situational questions, you can draw on a real past experience to ground your response while addressing the hypothetical scenario."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-formats.ts
msgid "Yes, the terms are used interchangeably. A chronological resume lists your work experience in reverse chronological order, meaning your most recent position appears first. This is the standard and expected format in most industries. When someone refers to a \"chronological resume,\" they almost always mean the reverse chronological format rather than a forward chronological listing."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/resume-fundamentals.ts
msgid "Yes, using a professional resume template is a smart strategy for most job seekers. A well-designed template ensures consistent formatting, proper structure, and ATS compatibility, saving you time and reducing the risk of layout errors. The key is choosing a clean, professional template that prioritizes readability over visual complexity. Avoid templates with excessive graphics, unusual fonts, or multi-column layouts that may confuse ATS software. Tools like IMTA Resume provide optimized templates that balance visual appeal with ATS compatibility."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid "Yes, using the same font for both your cover letter and resume creates a cohesive, professional application package. This visual consistency reinforces your personal brand and attention to detail. If your resume uses a font that is not ideal for a full page of text, choose a complementary font from the same family or with similar characteristics."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/ats-optimization.ts
msgid "Yes, you can use color in your resume without affecting ATS parsing. ATS systems read text content, not visual styling, so colored headings, accent lines, or colored text will not cause parsing errors. However, use color judiciously and ensure that all text remains readable when printed in black and white, as some recruiters will print your resume on a standard printer. Avoid using color as the sole way to convey information, such as color-coded skill levels, since this information will be invisible to the ATS."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/cover-letters.ts
msgid "Yes, you should almost always include a cover letter even when it is listed as optional. Research consistently shows that the majority of hiring managers still read cover letters and view them favorably. An optional cover letter is an opportunity to differentiate yourself from candidates who skip it. The only exception is if the application system explicitly does not allow cover letter uploads."
msgstr ""

#: src/data/wiki/categories/remote-work.ts
msgid "Yes, you should customize your resume for each application, just as you would for in-office roles. Tailor your professional summary, keywords, and emphasized skills to match each specific job posting. However, you can maintain a master remote resume template that includes all your remote-relevant experience and skills, then select the most relevant elements for each application."
msgstr ""

#: src/routes/_home/help.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes! After adding a preset, you can edit, delete, or reorder any skills. Adjust proficiency levels to match your actual abilities. Add more skills manually to customize your list."
#~ msgstr "Oui ! Après avoir ajouté un préréglage, vous pouvez modifier, supprimer ou réorganiser n'importe quelle compétence. Ajustez les niveaux de compétence pour correspondre à vos capacités réelles. Ajoutez plus de compétences manuellement pour personnaliser votre liste."

#: src/routes/_home/-sections/faq.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes! Every template is fully customizable. You can change colors, fonts, spacing, and even write custom CSS for complete control over your resume's appearance."
#~ msgstr "Oui ! Chaque modèle est entièrement personnalisable. Vous pouvez modifier les couleurs, les polices, l'espacement et même écrire des feuilles de style CSS personnalisées pour un contrôle total de l'apparence de votre CV."

#: src/routes/_home/help.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes! IMTA training is valuable. In Education, describe your program and key coursework. In Experience or a separate Training section, detail any hands-on projects, simulations, or practical exercises."
#~ msgstr "Oui ! La formation IMTA est précieuse. Dans Éducation, décrivez votre programme et les cours clés. Dans Expérience ou une section Formation séparée, détaillez tous les projets pratiques, simulations ou exercices pratiques."

#: src/routes/_home/-sections/faq.tsx
#~ msgid "Yes! IMTA Resume is completely free to use, with no hidden costs, premium tiers, or subscription fees. It's open-source and will always remain free."
#~ msgstr "Oui ! IMTA Resume est entièrement gratuit, sans frais cachés, ni droits d'entrée, ni frais d'abonnement. Il est open-source et restera toujours gratuit."

#: src/routes/dashboard/help/-components/help-config.ts
msgid "Yes! The platform is completely free for all IMTA students and graduates. All features, including resume creation, interview preparation, and access to resources, are available at no cost."
msgstr ""

